Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value.

Message: Variable value not found in non-extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable must be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms cannot be added into non-extensible codelists.

Message: Variable value not found in extensible codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable should be populated with terms from its CDISC controlled terminology codelist, when its value level condition is met. New terms can be added as long as they are not duplicates, synonyms or subsets of existing standard terms.

Message: Coded and Decoded values do not have the same Code in CDISC CT when value-level condition occurs
Description: Paired variables such as TEST/TESTCD must be populated using terms with the same Codelist Code value in CDISC control terminology. There is one-to-one relationship between paired variable values defined in CDISC control terminology by Codelist Code value within the same value level condition.

Guidance provided by regulatory agencies states that eCTD submissions must include a define.xml file for each study in Module 4 (nonclinical) and Module 5 (clinical). Note: Refer to the data standards catalog by the relevant Regulatory Agency for acceptance of standards and their versions.
Domain table should have at least one record.

Message: NULL value in variable marked as Required
Description: Required variables (where Core attribute is 'Req') cannot be NULL for any records.
Value of Dates/Time variables (*DTC) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.
Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN) variable should be consistent with the name of the dataset.

The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Pool Identifier (POOLID) or Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) variables value when they are present in the domain.

Message: No baseline flag record in Domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have at least one baseline observation (--BLFL = 'Y') in EG, LB, MB, MS, PC and VS domains, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN') or were not treated (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

Standard Units (--STRESU) must be consistent for all records with the same Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Specimen Type (--SPEC) and Method of Test or Examination (--METHOD).

Message: Value for --DECOD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Message: Value for --DECOD is in incorrect case
Description: Case for the Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) variable must be sentence case using a Preferred Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Message: No qualifiers set to 'Y', when AE is Serious
Description: When Serious Event (AESER) variable value is 'Y', then at least one of seriousness criteria variables is expected to have value 'Y' (Involves Cancer (AESCAN), Congenital Anomaly or Birth Defect (AESCONG), Persist or Signif Disability/Incapacity (AESDISAB), Results in Death (AESDTH), Requires or Prolongs Hospitalization (AESHOSP), Is Life Threatening (AESLIFE), or Other Medically Important Serious Event (AESMIE)).
Study Day of Start of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDY).
Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--STDTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Event, Exposure or Observation (--ENDTC).
Non-missing Dose (--DOSE) value must be greater than or equal to 0.
Non-missing Duration of Event, Exposure or Observation (--DUR) value must be greater than or equal to 0.
Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.
The value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be no more than 40 characters in length.

The value of a Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) variable should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.
The value of Parameter (--PARM) variable should be no more than 40 characters in length.
The value of Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be no more than 8 characters in length.

One End Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or an intervention occurred. (E.g., End Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--ENDTC), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF), or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '') or Duration (--DUR) != '').

One Start Time-Point variable is expected to be populated when an event or intervention occurred. (E.g., Start Date/Time of Event or Intervention (--STDTC), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF), or Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRTPT) should not be missing, or Occurrence (--OCCUR) = 'N' or Completion Status (--STAT) != '').

Message: Missing value for --STAT, when --REASND is provided
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE', when Reason Not Done (--REASND) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --DTC, when --ENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) should not be NULL, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC) is not NULL.
Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--DTC) must be less or equal to End Date/Time of Specimen Collection (--ENDTC).

Message: Missing value for --ORRESU, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Original Units (--ORRESU) should not be NULL, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --ORRESU is provided
Description: Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should not be NULL, when Original Units (--ORRESU) is provided.

Message: Value for --STNRHI is less than value for --STNRLO
Description: Reference Range Upper Limit-Std Units (--STNRHI) value must be greater than or equal to Reference Range Lower Limit-Std Units (--STNRLO) value.

Message: Missing value for --STRESU, when --STRESC is provided
Description: Standard Units (--STRESU) should not be NULL, when Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STRESU is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should not be NULL, when Standard Units (--STRESU) is provided.

Message: Missing values for --STDTC, --STRF and --STRTPT, when --ENDTC, --ENRF or --ENRTPT is provided
Description: Start Date/Time of Observation (--STDTC), Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) should not be NULL, when End Date/Time of Observation (--ENDTC), End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) or End Relative to Reference Time Period (--ENRTPT) is not NULL.

Message: Missing value for --TPT, when --TPTNUM is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --TPTNUM, when --TPT is provided
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) should not be NULL, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --TPTREF, when --ELTM is provided
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) should not be NULL, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --DOSU, when --DOSE, --DOSTXT or --DOSTOT is provided
Description: Dose Units (--DOSU) must be populated, when Dose per Administration (--DOSE), Dose Description (--DOSTXT) or Total Daily Dose (--DOSTOT) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --ORRES is provided
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) must be populated, when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is provided.

Message: Value for variable not found in user-defined codelist
Description: Variable values should be populated with terms found in the user-defined codelist associated with the variable in define.xml.

Message: Value of Study Day variable equals 0
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not equal 0.
All values of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) should be the same for a given value of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD).

Message: Value for --OCCUR is populated for unsolicited Intervention or Event
Description: Occurrence (--OCCUR) may only be populated, when a given Intervention or Event has been pre-specified (--PRESP = 'Y').

Message: --STAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', when --PRESP='Y' and --OCCUR is NULL
Description: When no response is provided for Occurrence (--OCCUR) for a pre-specified Intervention or Event (--PRESP = 'Y'), then Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE'.

Message: Missing value for --TRTV, when --VAMT is not NULL
Description: Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) should be provided, when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is specified.

Message: Missing value for --VAMTU, when --VAMT is populated
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) should not be NULL,  when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--VAMT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --RESCAT is populated
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Units (--STRESC) should be provided, when Result Category (--RESCAT) is specified.

Message: Inconsistent value for QLABEL within QNAM
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM).

Message: Missing value for --ORRES, when --STAT or --DRVFL is not populated
Description: Status (--STAT) should be set to 'NOT DONE' or Derived Flag (--DRVFL) should have a value of 'Y', when Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) is NULL.

Message: Missing value for --STTPT, when --STRTPT is populated
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) must not be NULL, when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) is provided.

Message: Missing value for --ENTPT, when --ENRTPT is populated
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) must not be NULL, when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) is provided.

Message: Inconsistent value for VISIT within VISITNUM
Description: All values of Visit Name (VISIT) should be the same for a given value of Visit Number (VISITNUM).

Message: Inconsistent value for VISITNUM within VISIT
Description: All values of Visit Number (VISITNUM) should be the same for a given value of Visit Name (VISIT).

Message: Variable in define.xml is not present in the dataset
Description: Variables listed in the data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the dataset.
Variable Data Types in the dataset should match the variable data types described in SDTM.
Variables described in SDTM IG as Required must be included in the dataset.
Variables described in SDTM IG as Expected should be included in the dataset.

Message: Variable appears in dataset, but is not in SDTM model
Description: Only variables listed in SDTM model should appear in a dataset. New sponsor defined variables must not be added, and existing variables must not be renamed or modified.
Variable DataType in define.xml must match variable Type in dataset. Define-XML data types of 'integer' and 'float' match dataset type of 'Num', all other match 'Char'.

Message: Variable in dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Variables included in the dataset must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).

Message: Domain referenced in define.xml but dataset is missing
Description: Domains referenced in data definition document (define.xml) should be included in the submission.
Domain table must have a valid format (e.g., SAS transport (XPORT) v.5 or text-delimited).

Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Variable Label in the dataset should match the variable label described in SDTM IG. When creating a new domain Variable Labels could be adjusted as appropriate to properly convey the meaning in the context of the data being submitted.

Message: Subject is not present in DM domain
Description: All Subjects (USUBJID) must be present in Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: USUBJID/VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match SV domain data
Description: All Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) + Visit Name (VISIT) + Visit Number (VISITNUM) combination values in data should be present in the Subject Visits (SV) domain. There is an exception for records, where Status (--STAT) variable value is populated. E.g., --STAT = 'NOT DONE'. Another exception is for records, where Occurrence (ECOCCUR) is 'N' in EC domain.

Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').
Element Code (ETCD) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').
A value for Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be present the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) domain.

Message: No Exposure record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) participating in a study that includes investigational product should have at least one record in the Exposure (EX) domain, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL'), were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN'), or did not receive study treatment (ACTARMCD = 'NOTTRT').

The combination of Description of Planned Arm (ARM) and Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) values must match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening (ARMCD = 'SCRNFAIL') or were not fully assigned to an Arm (ARMCD = 'NOTASSGN').
Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) must have a valid value of Domains included in the study data.
Identifying Variable (IDVAR) must have a valid value of variables from a referenced Domain.

Reference record defined by Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) must exist in the target Domain.

Message: EX record is present, when subject is not assigned to an arm
Description: Subjects that are not assigned to an Arm (ARMCD='NOTASSGN') or are screen failures (ARMCD='SCRNFAIL'), or ARM=null, should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Message: AE start date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: Start Date/Time of Adverse Event (AESTDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Message: Exposure end date is after the latest Disposition date
Description: End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) should be less than or equal to the Start Date/Time of the latest Disposition Event (DSSTDTC).

Message: Duplicate USUBJID in DM within STUDYID
Description: The value of Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject across all trials in the submission. In the Demographics (DM) domain, there should only be one record per subject.

Message: Negative or zero value for AGE
Description: The value of Age (AGE) cannot be less than or equal to 0.

Message: Mismatch between IEORRES and IESTRESC values
Description: I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) and I/E Criterion Result in Std Format (IESTRESC) should have the same value.

All SUPPQUAL Domains records are associated with a single parent record and must have a unique combination of Study Identifier (STUDYID), Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Identifying Variable (IDVAR), Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) and Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) variable value. For all SUPPQUAL domain record all The QNAM variable should be unique for each parent record.

Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Message: RFENDTC is not provided for a randomized subject
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be populated for all randomized subjects, those where Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN' or null.

Message: Missing values for TEENRL and TEDUR
Description: At least one of Rule for End of Element (TEENRL) or Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be populated.
Results in Death (AESDTH) should equal 'Y', when Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT)  is 'FATAL'.
Outcome of Adverse Event should equal 'FATAL', when Results in Death (AESDTH) is 'Y'.

Message: Missing value for SEUPDES, when ETCD='UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) should be populated, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.

Message: Invalid usage of SUPPQUAL for non-general-observation-class Domain
Description: Supplemental Qualifiers special purpose dataset (SUPP--) can only be used to capture non-standard variables and their association to parent records in general-observation-class datasets (Events, Findings, Interventions) and Demographics.
The value of Subject Identifier for the Study (SUBJID) variable must be unique for each subject within the study.
Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) must be less than or equal to Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).
The value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.
Study Identifier (STUDYID) values must match the STUDYID in Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: CODTC is populated, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: The value of Date/Time of Comment (CODTC) should be NULL, when comments are related to a specific parent record or group of parent records in a domain (RDOMAIN, IDVAR and IDVARVAL are populated).
The value of Element Code (ETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Message: ELEMENT value is populated, when ETCD= 'UNPLAN'
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element, where Element Code (ETCD) is equal to 'UNPLAN'.
Value of Duration, Elapsed Time, and Interval variables (--DUR, --ELTM, --EVLINT, --STINT, --ENINT, TDSTOFF, TDTGTPAI, TDMINPAI, TDMAXPAI) must conform to the ISO 8601 international standard.
The combination of Element Code (ETCD) and Description of Element (ELEMENT) values should match entries in the Trial Elements (TE) dataset, except for unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').
Planned Order of Elements within Arm (TAETORD) should be NULL, when subject's experience for a particular period of time is represented as an unplanned Element (ETCD = 'UNPLAN').
Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.
Epoch (EPOCH) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset.
The combination of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD), Criterion (IETEST), and Category (IECAT) values should match entries in the Trial Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria (TI) dataset.

Message: VISITNUM value does not match TV domain data
Description: Visit Number (VISITNUM) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Message: VISITNUM/VISIT/VISITDY values do not match TV domain data
Description: The combination of Visit Number (VISITNUM), Visit Name (VISIT), and Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) values should match entries in the Trial Visits (TV) dataset, when they are planned visits (SVUPDES = NULL).

Message: VISITDY is populated for unplanned visit
Description: Planned Study Day of Visit (VISITDY) should equal NULL for unplanned visits, where Description of Unplanned Visit (SVUPDES) is populated.
Demographics (DM) dataset must be included in every submission.
Character values should not have leading space ' ' characters, or '.' as an entire value. The only exceptions are COVALn and TSVALn variables.
The value of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be limited to 8 characters, cannot start with a number, and cannot contain characters other than letters in upper case, numbers, or underscores.

Message: VISIT/VISITNUM values do not match TV domain data
Description: Combination of Visit Name (VISIT) and Visit Number (VISITNUM) in subject-level domains should match that in the TV domain with the exception of Unscheduled and Unplanned visits.
Relationship Type (RELTYPE) must be NULL, when Identifying Variable (IDVAR) is populated with a --SEQ value.

Message: Non-unique value for ELEMENT within ETCD
Description: Description of Element (ELEMENT) must have a unique value for a given value of Element Code (ETCD) within the domain.

Message: Non-ASCII or non-printable characters in variable
Description: Variables value must not include non-ASCII or non-printable characters (outside of 32-126 ASCII code range), limited to variables which values may be converted into new variable name or label (--TEST, --TESTCD, --PARM, --PARMCD, QLABEL, QNAM).

Message: Value for --STRF is populated, when RFSTDTC is NULL
Description: Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Message: Value for --ENRF is populated, when RFENDTC is NULL
Description: End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated for subjects with missing value for Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC).
A value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must have a unique value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) with the domain.
A value for Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Planned Arm (ARM) with the domain.
Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) should be populated.

Message: Missing value for --TOXGR, when --TOX is populated
Description: Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) should be provided, when Toxicity (--TOX) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --TOX, when --TOXGR is populated
Description: A value for a Toxicity (--TOX) variable should be provided, when a Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable value is populated and greater than 0.

Message: Non-unique value for TSSEQ variable within TSPARMCD
Description: Sequence Number (TSSEQ) must have a  unique value for a given value of Trial Summary Parameter Short Name (TSPARMCD) within the domain.

Message: --CAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Category (--CAT) should not be identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Message: --SCAT value is redundant with other variable values
Description: Value of Subcategory (--SCAT) should not be  identical to that in Domain Abbreviation (DOMAIN); Reported Term (--TERM); Name of Measurement, Test, or Examination (--TESTCD); Name of Treatment (--TRT); Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).
Values of Category (--CAT) and Subcategory (--SCAT) variables should not be identical.

Message: Time point for non-occurred event or intervention is provided
Description: Value of Start Relative to Reference Period (--STRF) or End Relative to Reference Period (--ENRF) should not be populated, when an event or intervention is marked as not occurred (--OCCUR='N').
All values of Short Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST).
I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'Y', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'EXCLUSION'.
I/E Criterion Original Result (IEORRES) must equal 'N', when Inclusion/Exclusion Category (IECAT) is 'INCLUSION'.
Only one of Dose (--DOSE) or Dose Description (--DOSTXT) variables must be populated on the same record.
Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL) value may have up to 40 characters.

Message: Non-unique value for ETCD within ELEMENT
Description: Element Code (ETCD) must have a unique value for a given value of Description of Element (ELEMENT) within the domain.
Both Identifying Variable (IDVAR) and Identifying Variable Value (IDVARVAL) should not be populated, when relating information to the Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Non-unique value for TAETORD within ARMCD
Description: Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) must have a unique value for a given value of Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) within the domain.
Records for subjects who failed a screening or were not assigned to study treatment (ARMCD is 'SCRNFAIL' or 'NOTASSGN') should not be included in the Trial Arms (TA) or Trial Visits (TV) datasets.
The value of Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable should be unique for each record within a subject.

Message: Missing MB dataset, when MS dataset is present
Description: Microbiology Specimen (MB) dataset should be included, when a Microbiology Susceptibility Test (MS) dataset is present.

Message: AESER is not 'Y', when AESOD equals 'Y'
Description: Serious Event (AESER) variable value is expected to be 'Y', when Occurred with Overdose (AESOD) variable value equals 'Y'.

Message: Dataset is not present in define.xml
Description: Datasets included in study data must be described in the data definition document (define.xml).
The value of Element Code (ETCD) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.

Message: Missing RDOMAIN value, when IDVAR is populated
Description: Value of Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable must be populated, when value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable is populated.

Message: IDVARVAL value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Variable Value (IDVARVAL) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.

Message: USUBJID value is populated, when RELTYPE values is populated
Description: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variable value should not be populated, when Relationship Type (RELTYPE) variable value is populated.
The value of Element (Description of Element) variable must be unique within Trial Elements (TE) domain.
All values of a Parameter (--PARM) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables.
All values of a Parameter Short Name (--PARMCD) variables should be the same for a given value of a Parameter (--PARM) variables.

Message: Dataset is greater than 5 GB in size
Description: Datasets greater than 5 gigabytes (GB) in size should be split into smaller datasets no larger than 5 GB.

Message: Missing IDVAR value, when RDOMAIN value is provided
Description: Value of Identifying Variable (IDVAR) variable must be populated, when Related Domain Abbreviation (RDOMAIN) variable value is provided, with the only exception of 'DM' value for RDOMAIN.

Message: Variable prohibited for use in SDTM
Description: Variables described in IG as inappropriate for usage must be not included in the dataset.

Message: Variable which can be used only in SEND
Description: Variables designed only for SEND pre-clinical studies must be not included in the SDTM dataset.
Variables described in IG as not recommended for usage should be not included in the dataset.

Message: Model permissible variable added into standard domain
Description: SDTM model variable may be added into standard domains according its domain general class, if there are no restrictions on their usage specified in IG.
Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents should be included in the dataset. E.g., EPOCH.

Message: Permissible variable with missing value for all records
Description: Permissible variable should not be present in domain, when the variable has missing value for all records in the dataset.

Message: Variable is in wrong order within domain
Description: Order of variables should reflect the order of the variables in the SDTM Model. Variables for the three general observation classes must be ordered with Identifiers first, followed by the Topic, Qualifier, and Timing variables. Within each role, variables must be ordered as shown in SDTM: Tables 2.2.1, 2.2.2, 2.2.3, 2.2.4, and 2.2.5.

Message: Variable length is too long for actual data
Description: Variable length should be assigned based on actual stored data to minimize file size. Datasets should be re-sized to the maximum length of actual data used prior to splitting.

Message: Missing --DY variable, when --DTC variable is present
Description: Collection Study Day (--DY) variable should be included into dataset, when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) variable is present.

Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated, when Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Collection Study Date/Time (--DTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided and both of them include complete date part.

Collection Study Day (--DY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --DTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --DY = (date portion of --DTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --DTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Missing --STDY variable, when --STDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable should be included into dataset, when Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) variable is present.

Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated, when Start Study Date (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both Start Study Date/Time (--STDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Study Day of Start (--STDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --STDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --STDY = (date portion of --STDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --STDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Missing --ENDY variable, when --ENDTC variable is present
Description: Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable should be included into dataset, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable is present.

Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated, when End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should not be imputed. It may be only populated, when both End Study Date/Time (--ENDTC) and Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) variables values are provided, and both of them include complete date part.

Study Day of End (--ENDY) variable value should be populated as defined by CDISC standards: --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) +1 if --ENDTC is on or after RFSTDTC; --ENDY = (date portion of --ENDTC) - (date portion of RFSTDTC) if --ENDTC precedes RFSTDTC.

Message: Invalid dataset name for split domain
Description: Split datasets must not have name of original domain. E.g., lbhm.xpt is a valid name, when lb.xpt is not a valid dataset name for split domain.

Message: High risk of truncated value for --TERM variable
Description: SAS v5 export format has a limitation on variables length up to 200 characters. If collected value was more than 200 characters, then SUPPQUAL dataset should be used to store additional 200+ characters. Variable QNAM should have --TERM1, ---TERM2, etc. values for those records. Value splitting should be performed between words or numbers. See SDTM IG #4.1.5.3.2 for details. This risk-assessment check is triggered based on assumption that if original value was truncated, then the actual data value length is exactly 200 characters.

Message: No Treatment Emergent info for Adverse Event
Description: A treatment-emergent flag should be included in SUPPAE according to the FDA business rule that states, 'A treatment-emergent flag should be submitted.'

Message: Missing --CAT value, when --SCAT value is populated
Description: Value for Category (--CAT) variable should be populated, when value for Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is populated.

Message: Missing --CAT variable, when --SCAT variable is present
Description: Category (--CAT) variable should be included into dataset, when Subcategory (--SCAT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --ENTPT variable, when --ENRTPT variable is present
Description: End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --ENRTPT variable, when --ENTPT variable is present
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when End Relative Time Point (--ENTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --STTPT variable, when --STRTPT variable is present
Description: Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable is present.

Message: Missing --STRTPT variable, when --STTPT variable is present
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Start Relative Time Point (--STTPT) variable is present.
Adverse Events (AE) dataset should be included in every submission.
Lab Test Results (LB) dataset should be included in every submission.
Vital Signs (VS) dataset should be included in every submission.
Exposure (EX) dataset should be included in every submission.
Disposition (DS) dataset should be included in every submission.
Subject Elements (SE) dataset should be included in every submission.
Trial Arms (TA) dataset should be included in every submission.
Trial Elements (TE) dataset should be included in every submission.

Message: Value for --BODSYS not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Message: Value for --BODSYS is in incorrect case
Description: Case for Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) variable must follow MedDRA sentence  case and be populated using a System Organ Class of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).
Trial Summary (TS) dataset must be included in every submission.

Message: Inconsistent variable length within split datasets
Description: Split datasets should have matching variable lengths for future merges. Datasets should be resized to the maximum length used prior to splitting.

The structure of Findings class domains should be one record per Finding Result per subject. No Finding Result with the same Test Short Name (--TESTCD) and the same Qualifier variables at the same timepoint for the same Subject (USUBJID) are expected.
At least one value of three variables Start Date/Time (--STDTC), Collection Date/Time (--DTC) or Start Study Day (--STDY) should be populated.

Message: Inappropriate usage of variables in CO domain, when comment is a child record of another domain
Description: In the Comments (CO) domain, the following Identifier and Timing variables are Permissible and may be populated as appropriate when comments are not related to other domain records (i.e., RDOMAIN and IDVAR variable values are not populated): COGRPID, COREFID, COSPID, VISIT, VISITNUM, VISITDY, TAETORD, CODY, COTPT, COTPTNUM, COELTM, COTPTREF, CORFTDTC.
Comments should be stored in Comments (CO) domain, rather than be put into Supplemental Qualifier (SUPP--) domains.

Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT values are populated
Description: Value for Age (AGE) or Age Range (AGETXT) variables should be populated for all subjects. The only exception for SDTM is for Screen Failures (ARMCD=SCRNFAIL) and Not Assigned (ARMCD=NOTASSGN) subjects, or subjects with ARMCD=null.  There are no exceptions for SEND.
Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be populated, when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Message: --ORRES value is populated, when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Original Result (--ORRES) variable is expected to be missing, when observation was not performed (Status (--STAT) is 'NOT DONE').

Message: Missing value for --REASND, when --STAT is 'NOT DONE'
Description: Value of Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should be populated, when Status (--STAT) variable value is 'NOT DONE'.

Message: Inconsistent value for  --ELTM within --TPT, --TPTREF and/or VISITNUM
Description: All values of Planned Elapsed Time (--ELTM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) and/or Visit Number (VISITNUM)

All values of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.

All values of Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable should be the same for a given value of Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable, Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable, and Visit Number (VISITNUM) variable.
Relationship Type (RELTYPE)  variable values should be populated with terms 'ONE', 'MANY', when Related Records (RELREC) dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets.

Message: Neither AGE nor AGETXT variables are present
Description: At least one of Age (AGE) or Age Text (AGETXT) variables should be included into Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Inconsistent value for QNAM within QLABEL
Description: All values of Qualifier Variable Name (QNAM) should be the same for a given value of Qualifier Variable Label (QLABEL).
A Standard Result value (--STRESC) is expected to be populated for Baseline records (--BLFL='Y').
Serious Event (AESER) variable value is expected to be 'Y', when either of Seriousness Criteria variables (AESCAN, AESCONG, AESDISAB, AESDTH, AESHOSP, AESLIFE, AESMIE) has value 'Y'.
A value for Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) must have a unique value for Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) with the domain.
A value for Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) must have a unique value for Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) with the domain.

Message: Negative value of Study Day variable
Description: Study Day variables (*DY) value should not be negative in Exposure (EX) datasets.
Character Result/Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) value should be NULL, when Derived Flag (--DRVFL) value is 'Y'.

Message: No Details info for AESMIE Adverse Event in SUPPAE domain
Description: When a description of Other Medically Important Serious Adverse Events category is collected on a CRF, sponsors should place the description in the SUPPAE dataset using the standard supplemental qualifier name code AESOSP.

The medical history dataset includes the subject's prior history at the start of the trial. Start Date/Time of Medical History Event (MHSTDTC) should be before Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).

Message: Missing --PRESP variable, when --OCCUR variable is present
Description: Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable should be included into dataset, when Occurrence (--OCCUR) variable is present. (--PRESP/Events) Used to indicate whether the event describe by --TERM was pre-specified on a CRF.  Value is Y for pre-specified events, null for spontaneously reported events. (--PRESP/Interventions) Used when a specific intervention is pre-specified on a CRF. Values should be 'Y' or null. (--OCCUR) Used to record whether a pre-specified event occurred when information about the occurrence of a specific event is solicited.

Message: Expected variable with missing value for all records
Description: Expected variables may contain some null values, but in most cases will not contain null values for every record. When no data has been collected for an Expected variable, however, a null column must still be included in the dataset, and a comment must be included in the define.xml to state that data was not collected.

Message: Inconsistent value for IETEST within IETESTCD
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD).

Message: Inconsistent value for IETESTCD within IETEST
Description: All values of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion Short Name  (IETESTCD) should be the same for a given value of Inclusion/Exclusion Criterion (IETEST).

The structure of Events class domains should be one records per Event per subject. No Events with the same Collected Term (--TERM), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Severity (--SEV), and Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR), Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) and the same Start Date (--STDTC) are expected.
Start Date/Time (--STDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).
Date/Time of Collection (--DTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).
End Date/Time (--ENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of End of Participation (RFPENDTC).
Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).
Start Date/Time of Treatment (EXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).
End Date/Time of Treatment (EXENDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).
Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value must be less than or equal to Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC).

Message: Missing value for RFXENDTC, when RFXSTDTC is provided
Description: Value for Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable value is provided.
Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) variable value should be populated. It would be NULL only in studies not collecting this info.

Standardized Result in Numeric Format (--STRESN) variable value should be equal Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value, when Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value represents a numeric value.

Message: RFSTDTC is not provided for a treated subject
Description: Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC) should be populated for all treated subjects, those where Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is not equal to 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTASSGN', 'NOTTRT', or null.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'ADDON' Parameter.
TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMAX'.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMAX' Parameter.
TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='AGEMIN'.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'AGEMIN' Parameter.
TSVAL value must be either ISO 8601 format for time period (e.g. P80Y) or null, when TSPARMCD='LENGTH'.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'LENGTH' Parameter.
TSVAL for PLANSUB record must be numeric.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'PLANSUB' Parameter.
TSVAL for RANDOM record must be 'Y' or 'N'.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'RANDOM' Parameter.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'SEXPOP' Parameter.
Trial Summary (TS) domain must contain only one record for 'NARMS' Parameter.

Message: Variable value not found in user-defined codelist when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated with terms from user-defined value level codelist as specified in define.xml file.

Message: Variable value is null when value-level condition occurs
Description: Variable value must be populated when value level attribute Mandatory='Yes' as specified in define.xml file.

Message: Variable datatype is not %Variable.@Clause.DataType% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level datatype must match the datatype described in define.xml.

Message: Variable value is longer than defined max length %Variable.@Clause.Length% when value-level condition occurs
Description: Value level length must not exceed the length as specified define.xml.

Message: Neither SPDEVID nor USUBJID values are populated
Description: Value for Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) or Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables should be populated for all records in Divice In-Use (DU) domain

The value of Sequence Number (--SEQ) variable must be unique for each record within a domain and within each combination of Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID) and Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID) variables' values.

Message: --RFTDTC is populated when --TPTREF is not populated
Description: --RFTDTC is defined as the Date/time for a fixed reference time point defined by --TPTREF, therefore --RFTDTC should only be populated when --TPTREF is populated.

Message: No Informed Consent Obtained record in DS domain for subject
Description: All subjects should have an Informed Consent record in the Disposition domain.

Message: --BODSYS is not populated when --BDSYCD is populated
Description: Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) must be populated when Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) is populated.
All values of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD).
All values of Body System or Organ Class Code (--BDSYCD) should be the same for a given value of Body System or Organ Class (--BODSYS).

Message: Missing --TPT variable, when --TPTNUM variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable is present.

Message: Missing --TPTREF variable, when --RFTDTC variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain, when Date/Time of Reference Point (--RFTDTC) variable is present.

Message: Missing --TPTREF variable, when --ELTM variable is present
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable is present.

Message: ECDOSE is not greater than 0 when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' and ECDOSTXT is null
Description: ECDOSE must be greater than zero when ECOCCUR does not equal 'N' , ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE', and ECDOSTXT is null. ECDOSE must not be set to zero (0) as an alternative method for indicating doses not taken, not given, or missed.

Message: ECDOSE is not null or greater than 0 when ECOCCUR = 'N'
Description: ECDOSE must either be null when ECOCCUR equals 'N', or ECDOSE must be greater than 0. ECDOSE would be greater than 0 (when ECOCCUR equals N) for records that represent specific dose amounts that are not taken, not given, or missed.

Message: EXDOSE does not equal 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'
Description: EXDOSE must be equal to 0 when EXTRT = 'PLACEBO'.

Message: Missing --TPTNUM variable, when --TPT variable is present
Description: Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable must be included into the domain, when Planned Time Point Name (--TPT) variable is present.

Message: --VAMTU is not null when --TRTV is null
Description: Treatment Vehicle Amount Units (--VAMTU) value must be null when Treatment Vehicle Amount (--TRTV) value is null.

Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when SS.SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Subject Status (SS) domain with SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'.

Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DD record is present
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Death Details (DD) domain.

Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AEOUT = 'FATAL'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AEOUT = 'FATAL'.

Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when AE.AESDTH = 'Y'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Adverse Events (AE) domain with AESDTH = 'Y'.

Message: DTHFL does not equal 'Y' when DS.DSDECOD = 'DEATH'
Description: DTHFL must equal 'Y' when there is a record in the Disposition (DS) domain with DSDECOD = 'DEATH'.
The value of Set Code (SETCD) should be no more than 8 characters in length.

Message: TSVCDVER is null when Reference Terminology is versioned
Description: The Version of the Reference Terminology variable (TSVCDVER) should be populated with the version number of the Reference Terminology, when that Reference Terminology is versioned.

Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DTHDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

Message: SSDTC is not greater than or equal to DSSTDTC, when SSSTRESC = 'DEAD'
Description: Subject Status Date/Time of Assessment (SSDTC) must be greater than or equal to Start Date/Time of Disposition Event (DSSTDTC) when the subject's status is 'DEAD'.

MBRESCAT is expected to be populated in all records where a microorganism has been identified (MBTESTCD = 'ORGANISM'), excluding records where MBSTRESC equals 'NO GROWTH' or MBMETHOD equals 'GRAM STAIN'.

Message: IDVAR equals --SEQ when IDVARVAL is null and USUBJID is null
Description: When the RELREC dataset is used to identify relationships between datasets (in which case USUBJID and IDVARVAL are left null), instead of relating individual records, --SEQ cannot be used for IDVAR because --SEQ only has meaning within a subject within a dataset, not across datasets.

Message: QEVAL is null when QORIG equals 'ASSIGNED'
Description: For subjective data (when QORIG='ASSIGNED'), QEVAL should be populated and the value should reflect the role of the person or institution assigning the value.

Message: ETCD equals 'UNPLAN' when SEUPDES is null
Description: When the Description of Unplanned Element (SEUPDES) is not populated, the Element Code (ETCD) should not be equal to 'UNPLAN'.
Planned Order of Element within Arm (TAETORD) variable value must be an integer.

Message: TSVCDREF is null when TSVCDVER is populated
Description: The Name of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDREF) must be populated when the Version of the Reference Terminology (TSVCDVER) is populated.

Message: TSVAL is not between 0 and 1, when TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'
Description: For the trial summary parameter Randomization Quotient (TSPARMCD = 'RANDQT'), the value must always be a number between 0 and 1, with some cases where the ratio might be equal to 1.

Message: Missing PC dataset, when PP dataset is present
Description: Pharmacokinetic Concentrations (PC) dataset should be included, when a Pharmacokinetic Parameters(PP) dataset is present.

Message: The combination of ELEMENT, TESTRL TEENRL, and TEDUR is not unique for each ETCD
Description: The combination of Description of Element (ELEMENT), Rule for Start of Element (TESTRL), Rule for End of Element (TEENRL), and Planned Duration of Element (TEDUR) should be unique for each Element Code (ETCD).
Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.
Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.
Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'OTHER'.
Test Code variables (--TESTCD) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.
Name of Treatment variables (--TRT) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.
Reported Term variables (--TERM) should not be populated with values of 'MULTIPLE'.

Message: Inconsistent value for TSVALCD within TSVAL
Description: Parameter Value Code (TSVALCD) and Parameter Value (TSVAL) should have a one-to-one relationship.

Message: ECDOSTXT is null when ECDOSE is null and ECOCCUR does not equal 'N'
Description: Dose Description (ECDOSTXT) should be populated when Dose (ECDOSE) is null, ECOCCUR does not equal 'N', and ECSTAT does not equal 'NOT DONE'.

Message: --TOX variable is present when --TOXGR variable is missing
Description: Toxicity (--TOX) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Toxicity Grade (--TOXGR) variable is missing.

Message: --TPTREF variable is present when --ELTM, --TPTNUM, and --TPT are missing
Description: Time Point Reference (--TPTREF) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Planned Elapsed Time from Time Point Ref (--ELTM) variable, Planned Time Point Number (--TPTNUM) variable, and Planned Time Point (--TPT) variable are missing.

Message: --LAT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Laterality (--LAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Message: --PORTOT variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Portion or Totality (--PORTOT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Message: --DIR variable is present when --LOC variable is missing
Description: Directionality (--DIR) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Location (--LOC) variable is missing.

Message: IETESTCD is not unique within TIVERS
Description: A value of Incl/Excl Criterion Short Name (IETESTCD) must be unique within a version of inclusion/exclusion criteria (TIVERS).
All values of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be the same for a given value of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD).
All values of Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) should be the same for a given value of Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD).

Message: Missing value for --DECOD, when --PTCD is populated
Description: Dictionary-Derived Term (--DECOD) should be populated when Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --ENRTPT, when --ENTPT is populated
Description: End Relative to Reference Time Point (--ENRTPT) must be populated when End Reference Time Point (--ENTPT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --STRTPT, when --STTPT is populated
Description: Start Relative to Reference Time Point (--STRTPT) must be populated when Start Reference Time Point (--STTPT) is populated.

Message: --REASND variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Reason Not Done (--REASND) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Message: --STAT variable is present when --PRESP variable is missing
Description: Completion Status (--STAT) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Pre-specified (--PRESP) variable is missing.

Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADDON parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADDON record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Message: Invalid TSVAL value for ADAPT parameter
Description: TSVAL for ADAPT record must be 'Y' or 'N'.

Message: TSVAL is populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist
Description: TSVAL should not be populated with a value from the ISO 21090 null flavor codelist, or synonyms of the values. The TSVALNF variable should be used to capture these values, not TSVAL.

Message: LBTOXGR is not a numeric value when a numeric scale is used.
Description: When a numeric scale is used (Grade 1, Grade 2, etc.), LBTOXGR should only contain the number.

Message: No timing variables are present in dataset
Description: All domains based on the general observation classes (Interventions, Events, Findings) should have at least one Timing variable present.
The value of DOMAIN should be no more than 2 characters in length, excluding Associated Persons domains.
Offset from the Anchor (TDSTOFF) variable value must be either 0, ISO 8601 format for duration (e.g. P80Y), or null.

Message: The TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter is not provided with TSVAL equal to null, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When the study population is healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with a null Parameter Value (TSVAL should be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the TDIGRP Trial Summary Parameter, when HLTSUBJI parameter equals 'N'
Description: When the study population is not healthy subjects (TSPARMCD = 'HLTSUBJI' and TSVAL = 'N'), the Diagnosis Group parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TDIGRP').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the CURTRT Trial Summary Parameter, when ADDON parameter equals 'Y'
Description: When test product is added to existing treatment (TSPARMCD = 'ADDON' and TSVAL = 'Y'), the Current Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'CURTRT').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the TRT Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Investigational Therapy or Treatment parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'TRT').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTMODEL Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Model parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTMODEL').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the INTTYPE Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Intervention Type parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'INTTYPE').

Message: TSVAL is missing for the PCLAS Trial Summary Parameter, when STYPE parameter equals 'INTERVENTIONAL'
Description: When the study type is interventional (TSPARMCD = 'STYPE' and TSVAL = 'INTERVENTIONAL'), the Pharmacologic Class parameter should be provided with Parameter Value populated (TSVAL should not be null when TSPARMCD = 'PCLAS').

Message: Missing EPOCH value, when DSCAT is 'DISPOSITION EVENT'
Description: Epoch (EPOCH) variable should be provided, when Category for Disposition Event (DSCAT) equals 'DISPOSITION EVENT'.
When Reported Term for the Disposition Event (DSTERM) is 'COMPLETED', Standardized Disposition Term (DSDECOD) should have the same value 'COMPLETED'.

Message: Missing 'DEATH' record for subject in DS domain
Description: All subjects who have Death records (SSSTRESC = 'DEAD') in Survival Status (SS) domain should also have death records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in Disposition (DS) domain.

Message: DSSTDTC for DEATH record is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: DEATH records (DSDECOD='DEATH') in the Disposition (DS) domain should have Start Date of Event (DSSTDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Message: No records for subject are found in DV domain
Description: Subjects who have DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL VIOLATION' or DSDECOD = 'PROTOCOL DEVIATION' records in the Disposition (DS) domain should have supportive records with details in the Protocol Deviations (DV) domain.

All records in the Disposition (DS) and Protocol Deviations (DV) domains should have the Start Date/Time of Event (--STDTC) equal to or after a subject's Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) in the Demographics (DM) domain.

Message: Missing value for --STRESC, when --STAT is null
Description: Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) value should not be NULL, when Completion Status (--STAT) value is NULL.

Message: No Treatment Emergent info for Adverse Event (missing SUPPAE)
Description: A treatment-emergent flag should be included in SUPPAE according to the FDA business rule that states, 'A treatment-emergent flag should be submitted.'

Message: Value for COUNTRY not found in ISO 3166
Description: Value for the Country (COUNTRY) variable must be populated using terms found in ISO 3166.
TSVAL for FCNTRY record must be a valid term from ISO 3166.
Variable Label in define.xml must match variable Label in dataset.
Dataset Description in define.xml must match dataset Description.
The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to Pool Identifier (POOLID).
The Related Subject or Pool Identifier (RSUBJID) value should not be equal to USUBJID.
Study Day of Observation (--DY) must be less or equal to Study Day of End of Observation (--ENDY)
Start Date/Time of Event, Exposure (--STDTC) must be less or equal to Date/Time of Collection(--DTC)

Message: AEOUT = NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, but an end date is provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) variable is populated with an end date for the adverse event. If the adverse event has an outcome of NOT RECOVERED/NOT RESOLVED, it is expected that no end date is available.

Message: AEOUT = RECOVERED/RESOLVED, but an end date or collected duration is not provided
Description: The Outcome of Adverse Event (AEOUT) variable is populated with the value RECOVERED/RESOLVED, however the End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) or Duration of Adverse Event (AEDUR) variables are null. If the adverse event has an outcome of RECOVERED/RESOLVED, it is expected that an end date or a collected duration be provided.
Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Subject Reference Start Date/Time (RFSTDTC).
Date/Time of Informed Consent (RFICDTC) should not be after Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC).

Message: TRLNKID value does not exist in TU domain
Description: A Link ID (TRLNKID) value for a tumor that is referenced in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Identification (TU) domain for that subject.

Message: RSLNKID value does not exist in TR domain
Description: A Link ID (RSLNKID) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Message: RSLNKGRP value does not exist in TR domain
Description: A Link Group (RSLNKGRP) value for a response assessment that is referenced in the Disease Response (RS) domain for a subject must also be present in the Tumor Results (TR) domain for the appropriate measurement records for that subject.

Message: Missing EPOCH value, when a start or observation date is provided
Description: The EPOCH variable is not populated, however either a start date or a collection date is provided. The presence of a start date or collection date for a record should allow for the EPOCH variable to be populated. Variables requested by the relevant regulatory agency in policy documents (e.g., EPOCH) should be included in the dataset and populated.

Message: EX record is present, when subject is not treated
Description: Subjects that are not treated (ACTARMCD='NOTTRT' or null) should not have any Exposure records. Run-in records (EPOCH='RUN-IN') are excluded from firing for this validation rule.

Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when RFXENDTC is provided
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when Date/Time of Last Study Treatment (RFXENDTC)variable value is provided.

Message: Missing value for RFXSTDTC, when subject is treated
Description: Date/Time of First Study Treatment (RFXSTDTC) variable must be populated, when subject is treated (ACTARMCD is not 'SCRNFAIL', 'NOTTRT', 'NOTASSGN', or null).

Message: Value for --DECOD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Standardized Medication Name (--DECOD) variable must be populated using a Drug Name from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --CLAS not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class (--CLAS) variable must be populated using ATC Text from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --CLASCD not found in WHODrug dictionary
Description: Value for the Medication Class Code (--CLASCD) variable must be populated using ATC Code from the WHO Drug dictionary version specified in the define.xml.

Message: AEENDTC for fatal AE is not the same as DM.DTHDTC
Description: Fatal Adverse Event records (AEOUT = 'FATAL') in the Adverse Events (AE) domain should have End Date/Time of Adverse Event (AEENDTC) equal to subject's Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) populated in the Demographics (DM) domain. Subject's Date/Time of Death info should be consistent across all domains.

Message: Missing values for --STINT and --ENINT variables when --TEST references 'T1 to T2'
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) and Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) should be populated when Name of Measurement, Test or Examination (--TEST) is over a time interval, 'T1 to T2', where 'T1' is represented by the value in --STINT and 'T2' is represented by the value in --ENINT.
Study Identifier (STUDYID) values should be consistent for all subjects in the Demographics (DM) domain for one study.

Message: Missing value for --ENINT, when --STINT is provided
Description: Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) should not be NULL, when Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) is populated.

Message: Missing value for --STINT, when --ENINT is provided
Description: Planned Start of Assessment Interval (--STINT) should not be NULL, when Planned End of Assessment Interval (--ENINT) is populated.

The structure of Interventions class domains should be one record per Intervention Episode per subject. No Interventions with the same Treatment (--TRT), Decoded Term (--DECOD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Route (--ROUTE), Location (--LOC) and Treatment Vehicle (--TRTV) values for the same Subject (USUBJID) and the same Start Date (--STDTC) are expected.

Message: --STRESC does not equal --ORRES when --STRESU is equal to --ORRESU
Description: Standardized Result in Character Format (--STRESC) variable value should be equal to Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) variable value, when variable values are numeric and Standard Units (--STRESU) and Original Units (--ORRESU) are populated with the same units or are null.

Message: ARMCD value not present in DM
Description: Arm Code (ARMCD) values defined in Trial Arms (TA) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Demographics (DM).

Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable MIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Message: Missing TM dataset, when variable RELMIDS is present in a dataset
Description: When the Temporal Relation to Milestone Instance (RELMIDS) variable is used in any dataset, the Trial Disease Milestones (TM) dataset must be present for the study.

Message: MIDSDTC variable is present when MIDS variable is missing
Description: Disease Milestone Instance Date/Time (MIDSDTC) variable should not be present in the domain, when the Disease Milestone Instance Name (MIDS) variable is missing.

Message: ACTARMCD/ACTARM are populated but ARMNRS is not populated
Description: When Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD)/Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ACTARMCD/ACTARM are null.

Message: ARMCD/ARM are populated but ARMNRS is not populated
Description: When Planned Arm Code (ARMCD)/Description of Planned Arm (ARM) are not populated, the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable must be populated with the reason ARMCD/ARM are null.

Message: ARMNRS is populated but ARMCD and ACTARMCD are populated
Description: The Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable should only be populated when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) are null.

Message: ARM is populated, but ARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must be populated, when Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Message: ACTARM is populated, but ACTARMCD is null, or vice versa
Description: Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) must be populated, when Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) is populated, and vice versa.

Message: ARMCD/ARM is populated for a subject not assigned to treatment
Description: Planned Arm Code (ARMCD) and Description of Planned Arm (ARM) must not be null for subjects who are not assigned to treatment. This includes Screen Failure subjects and Not Assigned subjects.

Message: ACTARMCD/ACTARM is populated for a subject who wasn't treated
Description: Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) and Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) must not be null for subjects who weren't treated. This includes Screen Failure subjects, Not Assigned subjects, and Not Treated subjects.

Message: ADSL Population Flags provided in SDTM
Description: ADSL Population Flags, which had standard Supplemental Qualifiers included in previous versions of the SDTMIG (COMPLT, FASFL/FULLSET, ITT, PPROTFL/PPROT, SAFFL/SAFETY, etc.) should no longer be used in SDTM.

Message: RFENDTC is populated when ARMNRS is not null
Description: Subject Reference End Date/Time (RFENDTC) should be null for screen failures or unassigned subjects. Therefore, when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated, RFENDTC should be null.

Message: Multiple disposition events for the same DSSCAT and EPOCH
Description: There should be at most one disposition event record per subject per Subcategory for Disposition Event (DSSCAT) per Epoch. If multiple disposition events are reported for a Subcategory for DSSCAT and EPOCH, the sponsor should identify a primary reason and use that to populate DSTERM and DSDECOD. Additional reasons should be submitted in SUPPDS.
Start Date/Time of Milestone (SMSTDTC) should not be null. The start date/time of the Disease Milestone is the critical date/time, and must be populated.
Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) should be populated when Reference Result in Original Units (--ORREF) is populated.
Numeric Reference Result in Std Units (--STREFN) should be populated when Reference Result in Standard Format (--STREFC) is populated.
Result or Finding in Original Units (--ORRES) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y', unless the record is derived (--DRVFL = 'Y').
Character Result/Finding in Std Format (--STRESC) should be populated when Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) is set to 'Y'.

Message: RFSTDTC is populated for subject who did not receive treatment
Description: RFSTDTC must be null when the Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) variable is populated (excluding values of UNPLANNED TREATMENT), which indicates that the subject did not receive treatment.

Message: No Disposition record found for subject
Description: All Demographics (DM) subjects (USUBJID) should have at least one record in the Disposition (DS) domain with only possible exceptions to subjects who did not receive treatment (ACTARMCD is null).

Message: No records for SCREEN FAILURE subject are found in IE domain
Description: All subjects with Reason Arm and/or Actual Arm is Null (ARMNRS) equal to 'SCREEN FAILURE' should have records in the Inclusion/Exclusion Criteria Not Met (IE) domain.

Message: ETCD value not present in TA
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned for at least one Arm Code (ARMCD) in Trial Arms (Trial Arms).

Message: ETCD value not present in SE
Description: Element Code (ETCD) values defined in Trial Elements (TE) should be assigned to at least one subject (USUBJID) in Subject Elements (SE).

Message: No subject identifier variables are populated
Description: At least one of the following subject identifier variables must be populated for each record: Unique Subject Identifier (USUBJID), Associated Persons Identifier (APID), Sponsor Device Identifier (SPDEVID), or Pool Identifier (POOLID).

Message: Multiple BASELINE records for the same test
Description: By its definition clinical baseline flags (e.g., last non-missing value prior to first dose) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with Baseline Flag (--BLFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC) and Laterality (--LAT)
MedDRA coding Preferred Term (--DECOD) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)
MedDRA coding High Level Term (--HLT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)
MedDRA coding High Level Group Term (--HLT) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)
Body System (--BODSYS) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)
MedDRA System Organ Class (--SOC) should be consistent for the same collected term (--TERM)

Message: Multiple --LOBXFL records for the same test
Description: By its definition Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) should have only a single record for the same test for subject. Therefore, each subject (USUBJID) should have no more than one record with  Last Observation Before Exposure Flag (--LOBXFL) equals 'Y' for the same assessment which is defined by Test (--TESTCD), Category (--CAT), Subcategory (--SCAT), Method (--METHOD), Specimen (--SPEC), Location (--LOC) and Laterality (--LAT)
The value of Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) should be no more than 20 characters in length.

Actual Arm Code (ACTARMCD) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('SCRNFAIL'),  or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('NOTASSGN'),  or randomized but not treated ('NOTTRT'), or received non-planned treatment ('UNPLAN').

Description of Actual Arm (ACTARM) values should match entries in the Trial Arms (TA) dataset, except for subjects who failed screening ('Screen Failure'), or were not fully assigned to an Arm ('Not Assigned'), or randomized, but not treated ('Not Treated') or received non-planned treatment ('Unplanned Treatment').

Message: Missing value for DTHFL, when DTHDTC is populated
Description: Subject Death Flag (DTHFL) value must equal 'Y', when Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) is provided.

Message: Missing value for DTHDTC, when DTHFL is populated
Description: Date/Time of Death (DTHDTC) should be provided, when subject died (DTHFL=Y).

Message: Unexpected MedDRA coding in the SUPPQUAL domain
Description: MedDRA coding info should be populated using variables in the Events General Observation Class, but not in SUPPQUAL domains.

Message: Value for --PTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Preferred Term Code (--PTCD) variable must be populated using a Preferred Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --LLT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Lowest Level Term (--LLT) variable must be populated using a Lowest Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Message: Value for --LLT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for Lowest Level Term (--LLT) variable must be sentence case using a Lowest Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Message: Value for --LLTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for Lowest Level Term Code (--LLTCD) variable must be populated using a Lowest Level Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --HLT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Term (--HLT) variable must be populated using a High Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Message: Value for --HLT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for High Level Term (--HLT) variable must be sentence case using a High Level Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Message: Value for --HLTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Term Code (--HLTCD) variable must be populated using a High Level Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --HLGT not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Group Term (--HLGT) variable must be populated using a High Level Group Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-insensitive).

Message: Value for --HLGT is in incorrect case
Description: Case for High Level Group Term (--HLGT) variable must be sentence case using a High Level Group Term of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml (Case-sensitive).

Message: Value for --HLGTCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
Description: Value for High Level Group Term Code (--HLGTCD) variable must be populated using a High Level Group Term Code of the MedDRA dictionary of a version specified in the define.xml.

Message: Value for --BDSYCD not found in MedDRA dictionary
